{{Infobox officeholder |name = Paul Clemente |image = |caption = |office = Member of the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] from the 14th district |term_start = January 1, 2011 |term_end = December 31, 2016 |predecessor = Ed Clemente |successor = [[Cara Clemente]] |birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1963|5|19}} |birth_place = |party = [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] }}
'''Paul Clemente''' (born May 19, 1963) is an American politician who served in the [[Michigan House of Representatives]] from 2011 to 2016. He represented the 14th district which includes Lincoln Park, [[Riverview, Michigan|Riverview]], [[Melvindale, Michigan|Melvindale]] and [[Wyandotte, Michigan|Wyandotte]] in the Downriver section of [[Wayne County, Michigan|Wayne County]].<ref name="housedems.com">{{cite web|url=http://014.housedems.com/biography|title=Rep. Paul D. Clementes' Biography|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903215531/http://014.housedems.com/biography|archivedate=2014-09-03|df=}}</ref>
==Early life== Clements is a lifelong resident of the district where his parents owned and operated Clemente's Bar, Restaurant and Bowling Alley. It closed in 2010 after 60 years in business. By that time, Clemente was a co-owner and manager.<ref name="housedems.com"/>
==Education and career== Prior to being elected, Clemente was an [[accountant]] at [[Coopers & Lybrand]].<ref name="housedems.com"/>
==Personal life== Clemente, his wife, and three children live in [[Lincoln Park, Michigan|Lincoln Park]].<ref name="housedems.com"/>
